`,t.jsx(e.h3,{children:"The support button"}),`
`,t.jsxs(e.p,{children:["Now that the wallet was set up, I could directly integrate the support button. This was also surprisingly straight forward as I could simply follow the documentation on how to ",t.jsx(e.a,{href:"https://wagmi.sh/react/guides/write-to-contract",children:"write"})," and ",t.jsx(e.a,{href:"https://wagmi.sh/react/guides/read-from-contract",children:"read"})," small contracts. To get the number of supports, I simply call the ",t.jsx(e.code,{children:"getLikesForUrl"})," function of the smart contract. To support the content, I call the ",t.jsx(e.code,{children:"donate"})," function of the smart contract. That's it. As every developer in the world, I spent too much time one the styling of the button, but otherwise it was simply an enjoyable experience."]}),`
