`,t.jsx(e.p,{children:"The situation, which is closest to superconducting qubit systems are Rydberg quantum simulators. In these systems the atoms are confined in optical tweezer and strongly interact when they are excited into Rydberg states , as such implementing interacting qubit systems. They share many of features, which are similar to ions and superconducting qubits. The Hamiltonian, which is implemented in these systems, is a complex Ising type model:"}),`
